{
  "texts": [
    "The method achieved a sensitivity of 90% for COVID-19 pneumonia and an accuracy of 83.6% when compared to non-COVID-19 pneumonia cases and healthy individuals.",
    "Li and Zhu 40 developed the COVID-Xpert technology, which leveraged chest X-ray radiography imaging properties from a larger dataset of pneumonia and normal cases, refined with a small number of COVID-19 patients, to identify coronavirus cases using CNN models.",
    "They utilized the DenseNet-121 deep neural network architecture for pre-training their models, addressing the lack of COVID-19 cases and improving the model's effectiveness.",
    "Instead of using a more general dataset like ImageNet, they trained the DenseNet-121 model on closely related datasets, specifically chest X-ray photographs with 108,948 samples.",
    "They tested the proposed model using 555 chest X-ray images categorized into three classes: 185 normal, 185 pneumonia, and 185 COVID-19 images."
  ]
}